3.10	Schrammel_accordion	Schrammel accordion	A Schrammel accordion (German: ) is an accordion with a melody (right hand) keyboard in the chromatic B-Griff system and a twelve-button diatonic bass keyboard. It is named for a traditional combination of two Violins, Accordion and Contrabass known as Schrammelquartet, the music being performed was called Schrammelmusik, in the Vienna chamber music tradition.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/8/87/Schammelharmonika.gif
